1
00:00:43,560 --> 00:00:45,520
Let go of me! Argh!

2
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:48,000
Get over here!

3
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:48,800
Get over here!

4
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:50,000
Hey! Stop right there!

5
00:00:53,600 --> 00:00:54,800
Help! Please!

6
00:00:57,080 --> 00:00:58,080
Hey!

7
00:00:59,080 --> 00:01:00,080
Hey!

8
00:01:28,360 --> 00:01:31,160
I've prepared a welcome gift for the new
Superintendent, sir.

9
00:01:32,759 --> 00:01:33,560
Thank you.

10
00:01:43,520 --> 00:01:46,039
Hurry up, bro. I've been waiting so long.

11
00:01:47,280 --> 00:01:49,120
And who told you to leave before me?

12
00:02:00,680 --> 00:02:02,440
This has nothing to do with you! Get lost!

13
00:02:03,680 --> 00:02:05,960
He's right. Get lost.

14
00:02:26,760 --> 00:02:27,560
Go!

15
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:29,200
Fine, just go!

16
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:40,200
Are you okay?

17
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:43,040
I'm fine.

18
00:02:44,640 --> 00:02:49,600
If you hadn't stepped in, I'd have been in
serious trouble.

19
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:52,520
What were those guys trying to do to you?

20
00:02:53,200 --> 00:02:56,920
They were trying to bite my neck.

21
00:02:57,320 --> 00:03:01,040
Bite your neck? Why would they want to
bite your neck?

22
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,200
What are they, dogs?

23
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:07,800
You really don't know?

24
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:09,080
I don't understand.

25
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:13,400
Never mind. But it's kind of strange.

26
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:20,560
You didn't have to help me, but you did.

27
00:03:21,880 --> 00:03:22,680
Weird, huh?

28
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:27,480
Yeah, let's forget it.

29
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:30,960
As long as you're okay.

30
00:03:31,640 --> 00:03:32,520
I'll be back.

31
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:37,760
Could I have your LINE ID?

32
00:03:38,840 --> 00:03:41,920
I'd like to thank you properly.

33
00:03:43,079 --> 00:03:44,440
I really want to thank you.

34
00:03:45,720 --> 00:03:47,880
My name is Sangnuea.

35
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:05,360
I'm Phatsa.

36
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:08,800
Thank you, P'Phatsa.

37
00:04:10,320 --> 00:04:13,560
If there's nothing, then disperse.

38
00:04:14,720 --> 00:04:17,120
You can get home on your own, right?

39
00:04:18,959 --> 00:04:20,880
I’ll see you later. I’ve gotta handle something.

40
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:55,760
You're late, big brother.

41
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:05,440
Where's Superintendent?

42
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:08,960
I already had the staff entertain him.

43
00:05:09,960 --> 00:05:10,760
Send it.

44
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:13,400
He was so stressed.

45
00:05:14,160 --> 00:05:15,960
So I took care of it and helped him relax.

46
00:05:16,440 --> 00:05:18,480
But he seems to like something like this anyway.

47
00:05:19,080 --> 00:05:21,040
I was just serving him.

48
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:22,400
You're it.

49
00:05:22,560 --> 00:05:23,480
Are you going to see?

50
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:25,960
In case you want to know our new partner.

51
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:28,320
To know what he likes in particular.

52
00:05:32,320 --> 00:05:33,120
All right.

53
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:35,400
Follow me

54
00:06:01,880 --> 00:06:03,640
Welcome drink, sir.

55
00:06:03,880 --> 00:06:04,680
Thank you so much

56
00:06:06,680 --> 00:06:07,480
Fine.

57
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:09,280
Whatever you need, let my guys know.

58
00:06:09,760 --> 00:06:10,680
I’m off, then. See you.

59
00:08:56,560 --> 00:09:01,440
P'Ongsa, we're done. Would you like some
coffee?

60
00:09:02,040 --> 00:09:07,600
You already drank. We'll go wash the glass over there.

61
00:09:16,520 --> 00:09:17,760
I'm back!

62
00:09:18,640 --> 00:09:19,760
Phatsa

63
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:22,640
Would you like some coffee, P'Phatsa?

64
00:09:23,600 --> 00:09:25,360
Sure. Make me a cup, bro.

65
00:09:26,320 --> 00:09:27,120
Yes, sir.

66
00:09:28,560 --> 00:09:29,680
Are you here?

67
00:09:30,520 --> 00:09:32,080
Oh, Ongha

68
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:35,800
What are you doing?

69
00:09:38,680 --> 00:09:41,360
Where have you been? You're a mess.

70
00:09:42,560 --> 00:09:48,200
There is a bit of a story that I am practicing as a good citizen.

71
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:51,360
What? Good citizen?

72
00:09:52,280 --> 00:09:56,840
I helped someone. A kid was getting
jumped.

73
00:09:56,920 --> 00:10:00,800
I thought I'd play the hero for once.

74
00:10:01,680 --> 00:10:03,400
Or secretly having an affair?

75
00:10:03,960 --> 00:10:05,080
Where is it?

76
00:10:06,040 --> 00:10:07,240
But it's weird

77
00:10:07,800 --> 00:10:09,840
It was not intended to threaten money.

78
00:10:11,080 --> 00:10:16,920
They weren't robbing him. They just wanted
to bite his neck.

79
00:10:17,240 --> 00:10:18,320
Bite your neck

80
00:10:19,280 --> 00:10:20,080
Yeah.

81
00:10:21,520 --> 00:10:22,760
I'm still confused.

82
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:25,320
You are confused too, right?

83
00:10:25,920 --> 00:10:27,880
Maybe you helped an Omega.

84
00:10:28,520 --> 00:10:29,320
Huh?

85
00:10:31,240 --> 00:10:32,360
An Omega? What's that?

86
00:10:33,040 --> 00:10:35,160
Someone with a secondary gender. They may
have been running from Alphas.

87
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:39,000
He's probably being bitten by the Alphas.

88
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:41,120
Alpha, what else?

89
00:10:41,840 --> 00:10:43,160
Omega, Alpha.

90
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:44,840
What are you talking about?

91
00:10:45,360 --> 00:10:46,560
Secondary gender.

92
00:10:48,440 --> 00:10:49,720
What are you talking about?

93
00:10:50,240 --> 00:10:56,040
Most people are simply male or female.

94
00:10:56,720 --> 00:10:57,520
Yeah.

95
00:10:57,600 --> 00:11:04,200
But some carry a secondary gender
inherited from the Wolf Deity bloodline.

96
00:11:04,560 --> 00:11:05,360
Hey.

97
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:08,000
A wolf?

98
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:16,200
Want a donut, bro?

99
00:11:18,520 --> 00:11:23,080
So yummy, but unfortunately, Diet now.

100
00:11:25,960 --> 00:11:27,040
Do you want degrees?

101
00:11:27,480 --> 00:11:28,520
Come, come, come, come.

102
00:11:32,760 --> 00:11:37,560
You might be an Alpha.

103
00:11:39,320 --> 00:11:40,200
Why?

104
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:42,840
You're talented, smart, and a natural
leader.

105
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:49,960
Yes, elder Ban is good and smart, finishing with magna cum laude.

106
00:11:50,840 --> 00:11:55,480
First-class honors, Faculty Moon, and a
university athlete.

107
00:11:56,640 --> 00:11:59,000
Wow, awesome.

108
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:00,680
Speak well

109
00:12:00,960 --> 00:12:01,960
Come to arrange

110
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:11,560
You could be an Alpha.

111
00:12:12,640 --> 00:12:13,800
Alpha?

112
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:16,440
I don't think that's right.

113
00:12:17,800 --> 00:12:20,840
I've never smelled anyone's pheromones or
wanted to bite anyone.

114
00:12:23,720 --> 00:12:24,520
Hey!

115
00:12:26,880 --> 00:12:28,360
Though I once smelled someone...

116
00:12:31,040 --> 00:12:33,000
Nile when he hadn't showered.

117
00:12:35,080 --> 00:12:36,400
You showered? Could’ve fooled me.

118
00:12:38,840 --> 00:12:39,640
Whoa.

119
00:12:40,240 --> 00:12:42,520
Hey! I still smelled good.

120
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:50,160
Sorry, I'll make your coffee right now.

121
00:12:50,920 --> 00:12:51,720
Hurry up.

122
00:12:59,560 --> 00:13:00,800
Thank you, bro.

123
00:13:01,120 --> 00:13:06,480
Hey, Phatsa, this one of that one of his clients

124
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,080
Coffee now.

125
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:17,800
Thanks. That's mine.

126
00:13:19,440 --> 00:13:20,240
Yeah.

127
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:27,320
Why didn't you tell me?

128
00:13:28,080 --> 00:13:29,440
Mine tastes better.

129
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:30,840
Really? Really?

130
00:13:36,320 --> 00:13:37,160
When is he getting here?

131
00:13:38,800 --> 00:13:39,720
He's here.

132
00:13:40,880 --> 00:13:41,720
Your coffee, sir.

133
00:14:09,840 --> 00:14:11,040
Where's the coffee bought?

134
00:14:11,840 --> 00:14:12,960
Where did you buy this coffee?

135
00:14:13,040 --> 00:14:15,240
The same place as always. Everything's
exactly the same.

136
00:14:21,520 --> 00:14:22,760
It's nothing.

137
00:14:23,880 --> 00:14:25,040
The scent isn't the same.

138
00:14:33,680 --> 00:14:36,720
Same beans. Same barista.

139
00:14:39,120 --> 00:14:40,240
We should get going.

140
00:15:36,560 --> 00:15:37,360
Sila.

141
00:15:37,560 --> 00:15:38,360
Yes, sir.

142
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:43,680
Check the CCTV footage for me. I want to
know who that was.

143
00:15:45,920 --> 00:15:46,720
Yes.

144
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:17,400
Here.

145
00:16:22,840 --> 00:16:24,560
Is this the only camera angle?

146
00:16:24,960 --> 00:16:27,360
The café only has a camera at the cashier
counter.

147
00:16:27,960 --> 00:16:29,960
Find out who he is.

148
00:16:33,120 --> 00:16:34,160
Is something wrong?

149
00:16:42,240 --> 00:16:43,280
Please excuse me, I’ll take my leave.

150
00:17:53,480 --> 00:17:55,680
Get down! If you don't, we'll shoot!

151
00:17:56,720 --> 00:17:57,600
Get down!

152
00:17:58,120 --> 00:17:59,080
They're back again.

153
00:17:59,200 --> 00:18:00,080
Get down!

154
00:18:00,680 --> 00:18:01,840
How annoying.

155
00:18:10,120 --> 00:18:10,920
Raise your hands.

156
00:18:17,080 --> 00:18:22,400
At least they've upgraded this time. They
even set up a roadblock.

157
00:18:23,560 --> 00:18:25,120
Still idiots, though.

158
00:18:25,640 --> 00:18:26,880
You bet with me?

159
00:18:27,440 --> 00:18:28,760
I give you no more than three minutes.

160
00:18:34,560 --> 00:18:38,000
Poor guys outside. They picked the wrong
day to die.

161
00:18:38,920 --> 00:18:42,760
It's considered to eliminate fools from the system.

162
00:18:44,920 --> 00:18:46,360
Speaking of choosing people...

163
00:18:46,440 --> 00:18:48,880
When are you going to let someone into
your life?

164
00:18:52,080 --> 00:18:53,120
Don't start it.

165
00:18:54,760 --> 00:18:56,160
I'm getting serious.

166
00:18:57,640 --> 00:19:00,000
If you don't have a girlfriend

167
00:19:00,760 --> 00:19:02,280
Will be caught to see

168
00:19:04,040 --> 00:19:06,640
I'm not interested in anyone.

169
00:19:07,120 --> 00:19:10,320
Even if you don't want to marry one day, you have to marry anyway.

170
00:19:13,920 --> 00:19:16,080
If I ever meet someone who makes me want
to marry, then we'll talk.

171
00:19:16,800 --> 00:19:17,840
Then said

172
00:19:27,080 --> 00:19:27,880
It's done.

173
00:19:47,760 --> 00:19:52,360
Who sent you? I asked. Who sent you?

174
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:05,720
If it doesn't want to talk,

175
00:20:06,320 --> 00:20:07,800
Causing him to not speak again

176
00:20:24,680 --> 00:20:27,000
There have been too many attempts on your
life lately. Be careful.

177
00:20:27,480 --> 00:20:28,400
Be careful of yourself.

178
00:20:29,280 --> 00:20:30,680
And tell me.

179
00:20:32,560 --> 00:20:33,360
Not necessary

180
00:20:34,520 --> 00:20:35,400
Brother.

181
00:20:38,640 --> 00:20:40,560
I don't want Father to think I'm weak.

182
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:43,920
Or can't handle your own problems.

183
00:20:46,040 --> 00:20:47,880
But what if it gets heavier?

184
00:20:50,440 --> 00:20:52,200
I'll handle it myself.

185
00:20:57,200 --> 00:20:58,280
Up to each other

186
00:21:00,200 --> 00:21:02,040
But if you haven't found anyone yet

187
00:21:03,040 --> 00:21:06,200
Be careful, Mom will find a wife before you get shot dead first.

188
00:21:08,480 --> 00:21:09,280
Get in the car.

189
00:21:23,840 --> 00:21:25,040
Come have breakfast, dear.

190
00:21:27,360 --> 00:21:31,200
Jim, prepare breakfast for Nakhun and Nakhin too.

191
00:21:31,200 --> 00:21:37,520
Would you like breakfast or fish porridge?

192
00:21:38,600 --> 00:21:42,080
Fish porridge for me.

193
00:21:42,800 --> 00:21:44,160
I'll have the same.

194
00:21:44,320 --> 00:21:45,120
Yeah.

195
00:22:33,680 --> 00:22:36,520
Prepare something for Naphit too.

196
00:22:36,880 --> 00:22:38,920
What should you eat?

197
00:22:41,480 --> 00:22:42,280
Anything is fine.

198
00:23:10,360 --> 00:23:12,800
Hello, beautiful. What can I get for you
today?

199
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:15,240
One pink milk, please.

200
00:23:15,800 --> 00:23:22,360
We just got fresh donuts. Interested?

201
00:23:22,520 --> 00:23:25,120
Then I'll take two donuts too.

202
00:23:25,360 --> 00:23:28,320
Can take two donuts straight away

203
00:23:31,200 --> 00:23:32,280
Here you go. Enjoy.

204
00:23:34,080 --> 00:23:35,040
Eat well.

205
00:23:41,640 --> 00:23:43,040
Oh hello

206
00:23:47,120 --> 00:23:48,440
What's up, Bo?

207
00:23:49,880 --> 00:23:54,240
Hi, wait a moment. Just write down the order.

208
00:23:55,480 --> 00:23:59,120
Business is booming. At this rate you'll
be rich.

209
00:24:11,240 --> 00:24:13,040
P'Phatsa.

210
00:24:16,360 --> 00:24:19,080
What are you doing here?

211
00:24:19,680 --> 00:24:26,440
I brought these snacks to thank you for
helping me.

212
00:24:29,160 --> 00:24:32,880
Hey, Don’t worry about it. It’s nothing.

213
00:24:34,200 --> 00:24:37,280
It may seem like a small thing to you,

214
00:24:38,040 --> 00:24:41,880
but it meant a lot to me.

215
00:24:43,920 --> 00:24:48,960
If you hadn't saved that day, I would have been terrible.

216
00:24:54,720 --> 00:24:57,400
Was it really that serious?

217
00:24:57,560 --> 00:24:59,880
If I'd been bitten, it would've been a
huge problem.

218
00:25:01,800 --> 00:25:03,200
It must be a big deal.

219
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:05,800
Neck arrangement

220
00:25:08,680 --> 00:25:09,720
Don't tell me that.

221
00:25:11,920 --> 00:25:13,240
Don't tell me you're an Omega.

222
00:25:15,800 --> 00:25:16,600
Yes.

223
00:25:21,840 --> 00:25:24,000
For Alphas and Omegas, a neck bite is a
very serious matter.

224
00:25:24,800 --> 00:25:27,160
Biting your neck is a big deal.

225
00:25:28,320 --> 00:25:30,920
If it's a bite to bond

226
00:25:32,800 --> 00:25:40,280
It's like marking someone as your own.

227
00:25:40,360 --> 00:25:46,080
Our pheromones become bonded.

228
00:25:51,360 --> 00:25:52,320
Seriously?

229
00:25:53,960 --> 00:25:54,760
Yes.

230
00:25:57,440 --> 00:26:12,600
I'd be tied to that Alpha for the rest of
my life.

231
00:26:20,400 --> 00:26:27,160
There's no way to undo it?

232
00:26:30,760 --> 00:26:36,800
No one has ever broken the bond.

233
00:26:36,800 --> 00:26:41,440
Unless one of them dies.

234
00:26:44,480 --> 00:26:45,840
In short, don't let it happen unless
you're serious.

235
00:26:47,600 --> 00:26:49,400
If not thinking of actually bonding

236
00:26:51,440 --> 00:26:53,080
Don't let that happen.

237
00:26:54,320 --> 00:26:56,480
If you hadn't saved me, I'd already have
been bitten.

238
00:26:58,400 --> 00:27:00,760
I’m done for.

239
00:27:08,400 --> 00:27:09,200
Yeah.

240
00:27:10,240 --> 00:27:11,240
You're welcome.

241
00:27:11,880 --> 00:27:12,680
Thank you

242
00:27:14,680 --> 00:27:18,320
No, I'm the one who should thank you.

243
00:27:19,880 --> 00:27:20,680
Thank you

244
00:27:27,000 --> 00:27:27,840
Okay.

245
00:27:29,840 --> 00:27:30,680
P’Ongsa.

246
00:27:34,960 --> 00:27:36,480
Can you pop this in the fridge for me?

247
00:27:37,000 --> 00:27:37,800
All right.

248
00:27:38,080 --> 00:27:38,880
Thank you

249
00:27:51,000 --> 00:27:52,560
Well, it's like this.

250
00:27:53,040 --> 00:27:56,240
Long ago, in an age when humankind knew only fire and shadow.

251
00:27:56,240 --> 00:28:00,080
there existed a tribe dwelling high atop the mountains above the clouds.

252
00:28:00,080 --> 00:28:04,800
the tribe of the Wolf Gods, guardians of the seasons, instinct.

253
00:28:04,800 --> 00:28:06,280
and the flow of life itself.

254
00:28:07,080 --> 00:28:09,800
They concealed their presence from the world,
yet they were never truly gone.

255
00:28:10,160 --> 00:28:11,960
But on the night of the crimson moon.

256
00:28:12,440 --> 00:28:16,720
one wolf god fell deeply in love with a woman from the warrior tribe.

257
00:28:17,000 --> 00:28:19,920
From the bond between instinct and heart.

258
00:28:20,080 --> 00:28:21,760
a child unlike any other was born —

259
00:28:22,760 --> 00:28:28,000
A human whose very blood carried the scent of an ancient bond.

260
00:28:28,400 --> 00:28:30,160
From that lineage.

261
00:28:30,160 --> 00:28:33,440
the first generations began to show unique traits, dividing into three distinct types.

262
00:28:34,200 --> 00:28:37,640
Alpha — the bloodline of dominance and command.

263
00:28:37,640 --> 00:28:41,200
Born with powerful bodies and an aura of authority.

264
00:28:41,200 --> 00:28:46,160
they emit a mysterious pheromone capable of seducing or subduing others at will.

265
00:28:47,880 --> 00:28:52,520
Beta — the closest to ordinary humans, retaining the balance of mind, instinct, and reason unchanged.

266
00:28:54,720 --> 00:28:58,120
Omega — the lowest rung in the social order.

267
00:28:58,520 --> 00:29:05,040
destined to bear offspring and preserve the lineage.
Blessed — or cursed — with beauty and allure.

268
00:29:05,040 --> 00:29:08,400
their pheromones can intoxicate even without intent.

269
00:29:09,200 --> 00:29:14,160
That's why I'm a Beta. I've never smelled
pheromones.

270
00:29:22,200 --> 00:29:23,120
But.

271
00:29:24,160 --> 00:29:29,680
Me neither. How could I be an Alpha?

272
00:29:41,040 --> 00:29:41,600
Sorry about that.

273
00:29:49,800 --> 00:29:50,640
I mean…

274
00:29:55,920 --> 00:29:57,040
I smell something strange.

275
00:30:11,680 --> 00:30:12,760
Strange?

276
00:30:14,400 --> 00:30:15,240
What does it smell?

277
00:30:18,920 --> 00:30:19,720
It's

278
00:30:22,480 --> 00:30:24,480
It's not quite like a normal Alpha scent.

279
00:30:26,920 --> 00:30:27,920
I’m not really sure.

280
00:30:28,680 --> 00:30:29,480
What do you mean?

281
00:30:31,720 --> 00:30:35,320
Maybe you should get tested for a
secondary gender.

282
00:30:39,720 --> 00:30:40,920
Is that really necessary?

283
00:30:43,400 --> 00:30:44,200
Yes.

284
00:30:45,360 --> 00:30:48,920
If you accidentally bite someone one
day...

285
00:30:49,360 --> 00:30:52,520
That Omega could suffer for the rest of
their life.

286
00:30:54,360 --> 00:30:55,840
You should get checked.

287
00:31:08,200 --> 00:31:09,160
Come on, I'll go with you.

288
00:31:13,160 --> 00:31:14,600
Can I have a glass.

289
00:31:18,760 --> 00:31:19,760
Phatsa?

290
00:31:26,240 --> 00:31:28,160
Phatsa?

291
00:31:33,200 --> 00:31:35,440
Huh? Right here.

292
00:31:41,760 --> 00:31:42,560
Uh...

293
00:31:42,600 --> 00:31:43,640
Sorry, P'Ongsa.

294
00:31:45,040 --> 00:31:47,280
It's okay. Don't worry about it.

295
00:32:25,200 --> 00:32:26,000
Hey.

296
00:32:27,200 --> 00:32:28,000
What the hell was that?

297
00:34:36,560 --> 00:34:37,280
Oh.

298
00:34:37,360 --> 00:34:39,199
Young Master Japan.

299
00:34:40,199 --> 00:34:44,320
Hello, P'Sila. Hello, Hia Nakhun.

300
00:34:49,600 --> 00:34:52,600
How are your parents?

301
00:34:53,159 --> 00:34:56,480
They're doing well. My father sends his
regards.

302
00:34:57,280 --> 00:34:58,080
Thank you so much

303
00:35:00,160 --> 00:35:04,920
Did your father receive the wine I sent?

304
00:35:05,360 --> 00:35:09,400
He did. Next time, come have dinner at our
house.

305
00:35:10,720 --> 00:35:12,280
I'd like that.

306
00:35:12,360 --> 00:35:16,520
But I have to go now. See you later.

307
00:37:07,200 --> 00:37:09,240
Mr. Phatsa, what's your surname?

308
00:37:11,280 --> 00:37:12,600
Rattanatharin.

309
00:37:13,080 --> 00:37:16,120
Please make a fist and place your right
hand here.

310
00:37:17,160 --> 00:37:17,960
Yes.

311
00:37:47,200 --> 00:37:48,160
Will it hurt?

312
00:37:48,600 --> 00:37:49,400
Just a little.

313
00:38:05,760 --> 00:38:06,560
All done.

314
00:38:09,640 --> 00:38:12,240
Apply pressure here for a moment.

315
00:38:12,680 --> 00:38:13,480
Yes.

316
00:38:15,680 --> 00:38:19,200
How long will I have to wait for the
results?

317
00:38:19,560 --> 00:38:25,720
The secondary-gender confirmation test
takes about three to four hours.

318
00:38:28,240 --> 00:38:29,240
Yes, thank you.

319
00:38:44,600 --> 00:38:46,600
I've settled things with the other party.

320
00:38:49,800 --> 00:38:51,000
Did you give me the money?

321
00:38:51,440 --> 00:38:53,000
Did you compensate them?

322
00:38:54,040 --> 00:38:54,840
Yes. They've accepted it and left.

323
00:39:00,680 --> 00:39:02,360
You should behave yourself.

324
00:39:05,040 --> 00:39:05,840
Don't lecture me.

325
00:39:07,480 --> 00:39:15,400
Your behavior reflects badly on both the
family and the company.

326
00:39:18,440 --> 00:39:19,520
Acting like this?

327
00:39:19,880 --> 00:39:20,680
What kind?

328
00:39:22,120 --> 00:39:24,200
So what?

329
00:39:25,000 --> 00:39:25,800
Do I have to be perfect like you two?

330
00:39:27,960 --> 00:39:29,200
No thanks.

331
00:39:29,320 --> 00:39:30,960
To hope for just a compliment

332
00:39:32,760 --> 00:39:34,160
Spending my whole life chasing scraps of
praise?

333
00:39:35,680 --> 00:39:36,600
That's like being a dog waiting for
leftovers.

334
00:39:40,320 --> 00:39:44,040
That's not my style.

335
00:39:50,280 --> 00:39:51,080
You can leave now.

336
00:41:04,800 --> 00:41:06,560
The results still aren't out.

337
00:41:54,080 --> 00:41:55,080
It’s probably nothing.

338
00:42:18,440 --> 00:42:19,760
If I really am an Alpha,

339
00:42:23,480 --> 00:42:25,920
will I suddenly grow fangs or something?

340
00:42:26,160 --> 00:42:27,160
Ha!

341
00:43:41,040 --> 00:43:42,320
Careful! You'll damage the merchandise.

342
00:43:58,160 --> 00:43:59,440
You!

343
00:43:59,480 --> 00:44:01,320
Stay out of this!

344
00:44:02,040 --> 00:44:03,400
What are you planning to do with that kid?

345
00:44:03,680 --> 00:44:04,920
None of your business.

346
00:44:23,920 --> 00:44:24,400
Sir!

347
00:44:25,480 --> 00:44:26,400
Are you okay?

348
00:44:29,440 --> 00:44:30,240
Thank you.

349
00:45:32,120 --> 00:45:32,840
Phatsa.

350
00:45:32,880 --> 00:45:33,880
Why are you so shocked?

351
00:45:34,360 --> 00:45:36,200
The results say you're a Pure Omega.

352
00:45:36,440 --> 00:45:37,600
You need to be very careful.

353
00:45:38,120 --> 00:45:39,920
Don't let anyone bite your neck.

354
00:45:40,560 --> 00:45:41,720
Don't be afraid.

355
00:45:41,760 --> 00:45:43,040
I'll take responsibility for you.

356
00:45:43,680 --> 00:45:44,480
Take responsibility?

357
00:45:44,840 --> 00:45:45,640
You can't go back.

358
00:45:46,000 --> 00:45:46,800
You have to stay here.

359
00:45:47,320 --> 00:45:48,120
I'm not staying.

360
00:45:48,480 --> 00:45:50,840
Think of him as another son of mine.

361
00:45:51,600 --> 00:45:52,280
Thank you.

362
00:45:52,320 --> 00:45:53,920
If you end up having a child with him...

363
00:45:54,480 --> 00:45:55,160
No way!

364
00:45:55,240 --> 00:45:56,600
I'm a man, damn it!
